== Rice ==

Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @Jasmine Rice{150%g} and cook for ~{12-13%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a lid and
leave to the side until ready to serve.

== Pickled Carrot ==

Meanwhile, trim and peel the @Carrot{1}. Use the #peeler{} to peel long ribbons
down the length of the carrot, stopping at the core.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the @Rice Vinegar{15%ml} and @Sugar{1%tsp} for the
pickle. Season with @salt{}, then add the carrot. Mix together well, then set
aside to pickle.

Halve any thick broccoli stems lengthways.

Drain the @Tenderstem® Broccoli{150%g} in a sieve.

== Honey-Miso Sauce ==

Pop the Tenderstem® broccoli onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with
@oil{}, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, then toss to coat.
Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the middle shelf until tender and crispy,
~{10-12%mins}.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine the @Miso Paste{15%g} and @Honey{15%g}
with a @water{1%tbsp}. Set aside.

== Charred Corn ==

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the @Sweetcorn{160%g} and cook until charred, ~{5-6%mins}. Adjust
the heat if necessary. Stir only twice during this time - you want the sweetcorn
to pick up some nice colour.

Once charred, add the sweetcorn to a small bowl. Stir in the @Sambal Paste{15%g}.
Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Set aside.

== Assembly ==

Halve the @Avocado{1} and remove the stone. Use a #tablespoon{} to scoop the
flesh out onto a #cutting board{}, face-down. Slice into 1cm thick slices.

Once the broccoli is cooked, add the honey-miso sauce to the broccoli and turn to
coat.

When the rice is cooked, stir through the pickling liquid from the carrots.
Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Share the rice between #bowls{}.

Top with the pickled carrot, sweetcorn and broccoli in separate sections.

Pour over the remaining sauce from the tray, then fan out the avocado in the
centre.

Drizzle the @Sriracha Sauce{15%g} and @Mayonnaise{2%tbsp} over the top to finish.

Enjoy!